   <note>This document is a letter dated May 4, 1814, from Cherokee agent Return J. Meigs to General John Armstrong, Secretary of War. Meigs writes in regards to levies brought against the Cherokee and asks for reparations. Meigs explains that many Cherokee warriors fought alongside the US against the Creek and thus deserve appreciation.</note>
